    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nCurrently `vim.ui.open` only checks for existence of `wslview`. which is part of an archived project: https://github.com/wslutilities/wslu\n\nhttps://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/e6ce067f02ed07501093e79dc56466fada8652a1/runtime/lua/vim/ui.lua#L181\n\nThere's another popular script: https://github.com/4U6U57/wsl-open\n\nThis makes `gx` on wsl always just use `explorer.exe` and brings up an empty file browser.\n\nThis also makes plugins not being able to rely on `vim.ui.open`, here's an example: https://github.com/obsidian-nvim/obsidian.nvim/issues/268#issuecomment-3069888167\n\nIf this makes sense, I can PR the changes.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\ncheck for `wsl-open` and use it.",
    "closed_at": null,
    "closed_by": null,
